President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring the third Saturday of each May as Armed Forces Day. In the proclamation, President Obama pays tribute to the men and women who have served in the military and acknowledges the sacrifices they have made to protect the freedoms of the United States. He also emphasizes the importance of fulfilling the obligations and providing the resources and benefits that these service members and their families deserve. The proclamation encourages the participation and cooperation of civil authorities and private citizens in planning appropriate observances for Armed Forces Day. President Obama urges Americans to display the flag of the United States at their homes on this day and encourages citizens to learn more about military service by attending local observances and volunteering at organizations that support troops and their families.